{
  "text": "Propofol (2, 6-diisopropylphenol) is widely used for the induction and maintenance of anesthesia [CITATION_1] . Recent studies suggest that propofol also exerts antitumor effects [CITATION_2] . Propofol was found to suppress HeLa human cervical cancer cell invasion [CITATION_3] . In addition, propofol induces autophagy in some organs [CITATION_4] , which has been shown to potentiate the antitumor efficacy of some drugs [CITATION_5] .",
